AWS Lambda – Complete Detailed Notes

1) What is AWS Lambda?

AWS Lambda is a serverless compute service.

It allows you to run code without creating or managing servers.

You only provide:
	•	Code
	•	Runtime
	•	Memory
	•	Timeout
	•	Trigger event

AWS manages:
	•	Server provisioning
	•	OS patching
	•	Scaling
	•	Availability
	•	Fault tolerance
	•	Logging integration
	•	Security integration

AWS Lambda automatically scales and follows pay-per-use pricing.  ￼

⸻

2) Why Lambda is called Serverless?

Serverless means:
	•	No EC2 creation
	•	No OS management
	•	No patching
	•	No manual scaling
	•	No infrastructure maintenance

Example:

Instead of:
	•	Create EC2
	•	Install Python
	•	Setup cron
	•	Configure logs

You just:
	•	Upload code
	•	Add trigger
	•	Run

⸻

3) Lambda Core Concept

A Lambda application revolves around Function.

A function is a block of code that runs when an event occurs.

Example events:
	•	File uploaded to S3
	•	API request
	•	Message in SQS
	•	EventBridge schedule
	•	DynamoDB insert
	•	Kinesis stream event
	•	CloudWatch alarm
	•	SNS notification

⸻

4) Lambda Architecture Flow

Basic flow

Event Source → Lambda Trigger → Lambda Function → AWS Service / DB / API

example:

S3 CSV upload → Lambda → Validate CSV → SNS Email

This is exactly like your S3 CSV validation + SNS project.

