9) Lambda Execution Lifecycle

Very important interview question.

Phases

1. Init Phase
	•	imports
	•	boto3 client
	•	DB connection
	•	global variables

2. Invoke Phase
	•	handler runs

3. Freeze

Lambda container waits for next request

4. Reuse

Same container reused → faster execution

This reuse is why we put:

s3 = boto3.client("s3")

Cost = Requests + GB-seconds

Example:
	•	1M requests
	•	512 MB
	•	2 sec runtime


15) Lambda Concurrency

Concurrency = number of requests running simultaneously.

Default:
	•	1000 concurrent executions per region  


Concurrency = RPS × Avg Duration

200 req/sec × 2 sec = 400 concurrency

16) Reserved Concurrency

Used to guarantee capacity for critical function.

Benefits:
	•	no starvation
	•	critical pipeline protection
	•	cost control
	•	throttle recursive issues


17) Provisioned Concurrency

Used to reduce cold starts.

Best for:
	•	APIs
	•	login systems
	•	payment systems
	•	low latency apps


18) Lambda Layers

Reusable shared packages.

Use for:
	•	common utils
	•	pandas
	•	numpy
	•	internal logger
	•	auth utilities

